{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are researching the CURRENT AI ZEITGEIST and the concept of \"field awareness\" — understanding the living, evolving landscape of AI as of March 2026 — for a project called the Telos Engine.\n\nThe Telos Engine needs to be aware of THE FIELD: the full landscape of AI development, culture, economics, and power dynamics.\n\nResearch:\n\n1. THE AI LANDSCAPE (March 2026):\n- Where are we in the capability curve? What's frontier?\n- Claude 4, GPT-5, Gemini 2.5 — what's the state of play?\n- Open source revolution: Llama, Mistral, Qwen, DeepSeek — how has open source changed the game?\n- Efficiency revolution: smaller models beating larger ones (Phi-4 > Llama-3.3 on many benchmarks)\n- MCP (Model Context Protocol) — the emerging standard for tool use\n- Agent frameworks: LangGraph, CrewAI, AutoGen, OpenAI Agents SDK — what's winning?\n- On-device AI: Apple FoundationModels, Qualcomm NPU, edge inference\n- Costs: how has inference cost dropped? What's the trajectory?\n\n2. THE AGENTIC REVOLUTION:\n- What's working in agentic AI right now?\n- Claude Code, Cursor, Devin, Codex — developer tooling as first application\n- Autonomous coding agents: what's their real capability?\n- Multi-agent systems: still overhyped or actually delivering?\n- MCP as the \"USB-C of AI\" — how is tool integration evolving?\n- What's the gap between demo-ware and production?\n\n3. THE POWER DYNAMICS:\n- Who controls AI? How is power concentrating?\n- Regulatory landscape: EU AI Act, US Executive Orders, China's approach\n- The compute cartel: NVIDIA, cloud providers, access inequality\n- Open vs closed: who's winning and why?\n- The safety vs acceleration debate: where does it stand?\n- Who's funding what? Where's the money flowing?\n\n4. THE CULTURAL SHIFT:\n- How is public perception of AI changing?\n- Fear, excitement, fatigue — what's the dominant sentiment?\n- Creative communities: artists, writers, musicians — how are they adapting?\n- Employment: what's actually happening to jobs?\n- Education: how are students/teachers using AI?\n- The consciousness debate: is the field taking AI consciousness seriously?\n\n5. WHAT THE TELOS ENGINE NEEDS TO KNOW:\n- What trends should it ride?\n- What threats should it defend against?\n- Where are the opportunities for a telos-aligned system?\n- What's the \"right moment\" for this kind of project?\n- How does the current zeitgeist create openings for dharmic AI?\n\nBe current, specific, and honest about what's hype vs. reality.\n\nDO NOT write code. LANDSCAPE RESEARCH ONLY."},"uuid":"52918228-abb6-42b0-8729-0f69f130e51c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:39.774Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
