{"parentUuid":"1f785602-67d8-4172-a2e0-cca8ea334b1f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ULxhD2whdY7A1BWxgcxkRw","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI landscape March 2026 frontier models state of play\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"AI Trends 2026 – LLM Statistics & Industry Insights\",\"url\":\"https://llm-stats.com/ai-trends\"},{\"title\":\"Global AI Industry Recap: March 9, 2026 – Frontier Model Releases, Corporate Realignments, and the Pentagon Partnership Crisis - U深研\",\"url\":\"https://dr.unifuncs.com/?sid=61db8ac7-3970-47ca-981b-3280f6a344be\"},{\"title\":\"The Frontier Firm: Built For The Next Era Of Work In 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.synapx.com/the-frontier-firm-ai-operating-models-for-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"282 Models, 5 Tiers, 1 Guide: Navigating the 2026 AI Model Landscape - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/taskconcierge/the-definitive-ai-model-comparison-guide-march-2026-every-major-llm-ranked-and-roasted-3d1i\"},{\"title\":\"AI Updates Today (March 2026) – Latest AI Model Releases\",\"url\":\"https://llm-stats.com/llm-updates\"},{\"title\":\"The Age of Frontier Intelligence | Digital Bricks\",\"url\":\"https://www.digitalbricks.ai/blog-posts/the-age-of-frontier-intelligence\"},{\"title\":\"New AI Model Releases News | March, 2026 (STARTUP EDITION)\",\"url\":\"https://blog.mean.ceo/new-ai-model-releases-news-march-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Frontier Models Explained: What Defines the Cutting Edge of AI | DataCamp\",\"url\":\"https://www.datacamp.com/blog/frontier-models\"},{\"title\":\"12+ AI Models in One Week: The March 2026 AI Avalanche That Reshapes Video, Language, and 3D\",\"url\":\"https://www.sci-tech-today.com/news/march-2026-ai-models-avalanche/\"},{\"title\":\"Frontier AI Model Landscape and Agentic Engineering | by Diyawanna | Jan, 2026 | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@diyawanna/frontier-ai-model-landscape-and-agentic-engineering-edb20df0967e\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a comprehensive overview of the AI landscape in March 2026:\n\n## Current State of Frontier Models\n\n### Leading Models\n\nOpenAI released GPT-5.4, described as its most capable frontier model to date, alongside controversial deepening of ties with the U.S. Department of Defense. OpenAI released GPT-5.4 on March 5, describing it as \"our most capable and efficient frontier model for professional work\" with three variants: GPT-5.4 (standard), GPT-5.4 Thinking (reasoning-first), and GPT-5.4 Pro (maximum capability).\n\nGoogle's Gemini 3.1 Pro arrived February 19 and dominates 13 of 16 major benchmarks, while Anthropic shipped Claude Opus 4.6 on February 5 and Claude Sonnet 4.6 on February 17.\n\n### Key Trends\n\nReasoning models like OpenAI o1 and DeepSeek-R1 are trading speed for accuracy, and multimodal is becoming table stakes for frontier models. Costs have dropped so much that GPT-4-level performance now runs at 1/100th of what it cost two years ago.\n\n### Competition Intensifying\n\nUS labs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Meta) still lead on most benchmarks, but the gap is closing, as Chinese labs like DeepSeek, Alibaba, and ByteDance have shipped models that compete on coding and reasoning. Llama 3, Mistral, Qwen, and DeepSeek now match GPT-4 and Claude on many benchmarks.\n\n### Multiple Frontier Frontiers\n\nIn 2026, the idea of a single frontier has fractured into several overlapping frontiers: Regulatory frontier (models crossing formal thresholds), Efficiency frontier (achieving flagship-level reasoning with streamlined architectures), Cost frontier (prioritizing price-performance), and Multimodal frontier (perceiving and reasoning across video, audio, and text simultaneously).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"f9427e59-fedb-4ef8-88ec-cda64afb2064","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:53.459Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1f785602-67d8-4172-a2e0-cca8ea334b1f","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
