{"parentUuid":"b0bd2134-c5da-437f-ba26-9a8872acea89","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013rK7CFrnUMdg8yxyaMwLGy","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"open source AI models 2026 Llama Mistral Qwen DeepSeek revolution\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"10 Best Open-Source LLM Models (2025 Updated): Llama 4, Qwen 3 and DeepSeek R1\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/blog/daya-shankar/open-source-llms\"},{\"title\":\"LLM News Today (March 2026) – AI Model Releases\",\"url\":\"https://llm-stats.com/ai-news\"},{\"title\":\"Top 10 Open Source LLMs 2026: DeepSeek Revolution Guide | Articles | o-mega\",\"url\":\"https://o-mega.ai/articles/top-10-open-source-llms-the-deepseek-revolution-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Open Source AI Models In 2026: Llama Vs Mistral Vs DeepSeek Vs Qwen Compared\",\"url\":\"https://blueheadline.com/ai-robotics/open-source-ai-models-in-2026-llama-vs-mistral-vs-deepseek-vs-qwen-compared/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Updates Today (March 2026) – Latest AI Model Releases\",\"url\":\"https://llm-stats.com/llm-updates\"},{\"title\":\"DeepSeek and the Open Source AI Revolution: How Open Weights Models Are Reshaping Enterprise AI in 2026 | Programming Helper Tech\",\"url\":\"https://www.programming-helper.com/tech/deepseek-open-source-ai-models-2026-python-enterprise-adoption\"},{\"title\":\"15 Best Open Source AI Models & LLMs in 2026 (Tested and Reviewed)\",\"url\":\"https://elephas.app/blog/best-open-source-ai-models\"},{\"title\":\"Best Self-Hosted LLM Leaderboard 2026 | Open-Weight Model Rankings for Enterprise | Onyx AI\",\"url\":\"https://onyx.app/self-hosted-llm-leaderboard\"},{\"title\":\"Best Open Source LLM Leaderboard 2026 | Open Source Model Rankings and Tier List | Onyx AI\",\"url\":\"https://onyx.app/open-llm-leaderboard\"},{\"title\":\"Open Source AI in 2026: The Complete Guide to Models, Tools, and Frameworks | Miniloop\",\"url\":\"https://www.miniloop.ai/blog/open-source-ai\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a comprehensive overview of open source AI models in 2026:\n\n## The Open Source AI Landscape in 2026\n\nEighteen months ago, the gap between the best open models and the best proprietary ones (GPT-4, Claude 3) was large enough that the choice was simple. Today, that gap has closed to the point where the right open model, run correctly, can outperform proprietary alternatives on specific tasks.\n\n### Leading Models\n\n**DeepSeek Revolution**: When the Chinese AI startup released its R1 model in January 2025, it sent shockwaves through the industry—challenging assumptions about computational requirements, proprietary advantages, and the sustainability of closed AI ecosystems. Less than a year later, DeepSeek's open weights approach has catalyzed a paradigm shift, with enterprises worldwide increasingly adopting open source large language models for production deployments.\n\nThe company's V3 model, released in December 2024 and updated through March 2025, demonstrated that state-of-the-art AI capabilities need not require billions of dollars in computational investment. According to DeepSeek's technical documentation, the model was trained for approximately $6 million on a cluster of NVIDIA H800 GPUs—a fraction of the estimated $100 million or more spent training comparable proprietary models.\n\n**Meta's Llama**: Meta's Llama family has become the foundation for numerous enterprise deployments, with Llama 4—released in early 2026—offering improved reasoning capabilities and expanded context windows. According to Meta's AI blog, Llama 4 achieved 89% of GPT-4.5's performance on key benchmarks while enabling full fine-tuning on consumer hardware with sufficient VRAM.\n\n**Qwen & Mistral**: Alibaba's Qwen 2.5 family has become the go-to for applications requiring strong performance in Chinese, Japanese, Korean, and other Asian languages — areas where Western models still have meaningful gaps. Mistral's Mixtral is a powerful Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) model that uses 8 distinct \"expert\" networks and activates two of them for each token, providing massive parameter scale with manageable compute. This makes it incredibly fast and efficient for its size.\n\n### Market Growth & Impact\n\nAccording to Anthropic's analysis of the AI landscape, the open source AI market has grown 340% year-over-year in 2026, with enterprises deploying open weights models in production increasing from 23% to 67%.\n\nThe best open source LLMs in 2026 are DeepSeek-V3.2 (best overall), Llama 4 Scout (best for long context), Qwen 3 (best multilingual), and Mistral Large 2 (best for European deployment).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"e5a454e4-5a74-4f19-bac2-38d09051253d","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:58.463Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b0bd2134-c5da-437f-ba26-9a8872acea89","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
