{"parentUuid":"5c947f19-c1a5-41d5-8388-826cb9d01191","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_014jaV1nsKrECXB9NsZoMhFd","toolUseID":"toolu_014jaV1nsKrECXB9NsZoMhFd","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:09.466Z","uuid":"c69b5fe4-a6d3-495b-acc2-1bd66da6fa6b","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"2181516a-fb1e-471f-970e-fb4a64934566","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014jaV1nsKrECXB9NsZoMhFd","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"MCP Model Context Protocol adoption 2026 standard tool use\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Model Context Protocol - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_Context_Protocol\"},{\"title\":\"The 2026 MCP Roadmap | Model Context Protocol Blog\",\"url\":\"http://blog.modelcontextprotocol.io/posts/2026-mcp-roadmap/\"},{\"title\":\"Specification - Model Context Protocol\",\"url\":\"https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/2025-11-25\"},{\"title\":\"2026: The Year for Enterprise-Ready MCP Adoption\",\"url\":\"https://www.cdata.com/blog/2026-year-enterprise-ready-mcp-adoption\"},{\"title\":\"What is Model Context Protocol (MCP)? | IBM\",\"url\":\"https://www.ibm.com/think/topics/model-context-protocol\"},{\"title\":\"Model Context Protocol: A Complete Guide for 2026 | Fast.io\",\"url\":\"https://fast.io/resources/model-context-protocol/\"},{\"title\":\"Model Context Protocol (MCP) 2026: The Complete Guide - Calmops\",\"url\":\"https://calmops.com/ai/model-context-protocol-mcp-2026-complete-guide/\"},{\"title\":\"A Year of MCP: From Internal Experiment to Industry Standard | Pento\",\"url\":\"https://www.pento.ai/blog/a-year-of-mcp-2025-review\"},{\"title\":\"MCP 2026 | Model Context Protocol Complete Guide — What It Is, How It Works\",\"url\":\"https://sainam.tech/blog/mcp-complete-guide-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - modelcontextprotocol/modelcontextprotocol: Specification and documentation for the Model Context Protocol · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/modelcontextprotocol\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what I found about MCP Model Context Protocol adoption in 2026 and standard tool use:\n\n## MCP Overview and Adoption\n\nThe Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard and open-source framework introduced by Anthropic in November 2024 to standardize the way artificial intelligence (AI) systems like large language models (LLMs) integrate and share data with external tools, systems, and data sources.\n\n## 2026 Adoption Status\n\nAs we move through 2026, MCP has transitioned from an experimental concept to a production-ready protocol adopted by major AI providers and developers worldwide. Following its announcement, the protocol was adopted by major AI providers, including OpenAI and Google DeepMind. More specifically, in March 2025, OpenAI officially adopted the MCP, after having integrated the standard across its products, including the ChatGPT desktop app.\n\n## Growth Metrics\n\nOver 500 MCP servers are publicly available as of 2026, covering databases, file storage, web scraping, document processing, APIs, and more. Additionally, MCP adoption grew 340% in 2025, with over 500 MCP servers now available in public registries.\n\n## Standard Tool Use\n\nModel Context Protocol (MCP) is an open protocol that enables seamless integration between LLM applications and external data sources and tools. MCP solves this by providing a standardized protocol, turning this into an \"M+N problem\" where tool creators build N MCP servers (one for each system) and application developers build M MCP clients (one for each AI application).\n\n## 2026 Roadmap\n\nMCP's current spec release came out in November 2025, and it now runs in production at companies large and small, powers agent workflows, and is shaped by a growing community through Working Groups, Spec Enhancement Proposals (SEPs), and a formal governance process.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"d8835882-c46f-47f9-bd79-d8149ed2140a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:09.466Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2181516a-fb1e-471f-970e-fb4a64934566","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
