{"parentUuid":"ed9875af-0523-428c-8abd-e7e6768ad6fd","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MntNsyxn5sF2Wjxi3HPRya","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI agent frameworks 2026 LangGraph CrewAI AutoGen OpenAI Agents SDK comparison\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"A Detailed Comparison of Top 6 AI Agent Frameworks in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.turing.com/resources/ai-agent-frameworks\"},{\"title\":\"AI Agent Frameworks Compared (2026): LangChain, CrewAI, AutoGen, MetaGPT, OpenDevin + 6 More | Arsum\",\"url\":\"https://arsum.com/blog/posts/ai-agent-frameworks/\"},{\"title\":\"Best AI Agent Frameworks 2025: LangGraph, CrewAI, OpenAI, LlamaIndex, AutoGen\",\"url\":\"https://www.getmaxim.ai/articles/top-5-ai-agent-frameworks-in-2025-a-practical-guide-for-ai-builders/\"},{\"title\":\"LangGraph vs CrewAI vs AutoGen: Top 10 AI Agent Frameworks | Articles | o-mega\",\"url\":\"https://o-mega.ai/articles/langgraph-vs-crewai-vs-autogen-top-10-agent-frameworks-2026\"},{\"title\":\"CrewAI vs LangGraph vs AutoGen vs OpenAgents (2026) | OpenAgents Blog\",\"url\":\"https://openagents.org/blog/posts/2026-02-23-open-source-ai-agent-frameworks-compared\"},{\"title\":\"Top 5 Open-Source Agentic AI Frameworks in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://aimultiple.com/agentic-frameworks\"},{\"title\":\"AI Agent Frameworks 2026: LangGraph vs CrewAI & More | Let's Data Science\",\"url\":\"https://letsdatascience.com/blog/ai-agent-frameworks-compared\"},{\"title\":\"Best Multi-Agent Frameworks in 2026: LangGraph, CrewAI ...\",\"url\":\"https://gurusup.com/blog/best-multi-agent-frameworks-2026\"},{\"title\":\"CrewAI vs LangGraph vs AutoGen: Choosing the Right Multi-Agent AI Framework | DataCamp\",\"url\":\"https://www.datacamp.com/tutorial/crewai-vs-langgraph-vs-autogen\"},{\"title\":\"The Great AI Agent Showdown of 2026: OpenAI, AutoGen, CrewAI, or LangGraph? - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/topuzas/the-great-ai-agent-showdown-of-2026-openai-autogen-crewai-or-langgraph-1ea8\"}]\n\nI've found comprehensive information about AI agent frameworks in 2026. Here's a detailed comparison of the major frameworks you asked about:\n\n## Overview of Leading Frameworks\n\nLangChain combined with LangGraph remains the most popular by downloads and community size, with 47M+ PyPI downloads and the largest ecosystem of integrations. However, CrewAI is the fastest-growing for multi-agent use cases, and OpenAI Agents SDK has the lowest barrier to entry.\n\n## Framework Comparison\n\n**LangGraph**\nLangGraph is a powerful open-source library within the LangChain ecosystem, designed specifically for building stateful, multi-actor applications powered by LLMs, extending LangChain's capabilities by introducing the ability to create and manage cyclical graphs. LangGraph represents workflows as a graph with nodes and edges, offering a more visual and structured approach to workflow management.\n\n**CrewAI**\nCrewAI enables collaborative, role-based agent systems. CrewAI has the lowest learning curve with a role-based DSL, allowing you to define a working multi-agent system in under 20 lines of Python.\n\n**AutoGen**\nMicrosoft AutoGen supports next-generation LLM applications through multi-agent conversations. Microsoft merged AutoGen and Semantic Kernel into the Microsoft Agent Framework, which reached Release Candidate on February 19, 2026, bringing graph-based workflows, A2A and MCP protocol support, streaming, checkpointing, and human-in-the-loop patterns for Python and .NET.\n\n**OpenAI Agents SDK**\nThe OpenAI Agents SDK (version 0.10.2) now supports 100+ LLMs through the Chat Completions API, not just OpenAI models.\n\n## Key Differences\n\nThe biggest difference is the programming model—CrewAI lets you think in terms of people on a team, each with a role and goal, while LangGraph makes you think in terms of nodes and edges with state flowing through a directed graph.\n\n## Use Case Recommendations\n\nFor moderate complexity (3-5 agents, conditional routing), CrewAI or OpenAI Agents SDK will get you running fast, while for complex graphs with loops, parallel branches, and approval gates, LangGraph is the right tool.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"45986c2c-08c7-45d6-a45d-45f040a8a071","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:10.931Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ed9875af-0523-428c-8abd-e7e6768ad6fd","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
