{"parentUuid":"61a41e00-6d68-461d-8fe0-5281ebfa6a7a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QWU1gLGJRCiQMAzJbSzkDq","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Claude Code Cursor Devin autonomous coding agents 2026 real capability\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Best AI Coding Agents in 2026: Ranked and Compared - The Codegen Blog\",\"url\":\"https://codegen.com/blog/best-ai-coding-agents/\"},{\"title\":\"Cursor vs Claude Code: Which AI Coding Tool Wins in 2026? | IJONIS\",\"url\":\"https://ijonis.com/en/cursor-vs-claude-code\"},{\"title\":\"Cursor vs Claude Code in 2026: Which AI Coding Tool Fits Your Workflow\",\"url\":\"https://particula.tech/blog/cursor-vs-claude-code-2026-guide\"},{\"title\":\"The State of AI Coding Agents (2026): From Pair Programming to Autonomous AI Teams | by Dave Patten | Mar, 2026 | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@dave-patten/the-state-of-ai-coding-agents-2026-from-pair-programming-to-autonomous-ai-teams-b11f2b39232a\"},{\"title\":\"Best Devin Alternative in 2026: 7 AI Coding Agents Compared — Co-Founder\",\"url\":\"https://agentfounder.ai/blog/best-devin-alternative-2026\"},{\"title\":\"AI Coding Tools Compared (2026): Cursor vs Claude Code vs Copilot — Benchmarks & Pricing | TLDL | TLDL - AI Digest\",\"url\":\"https://www.tldl.io/resources/ai-coding-tools-2026\"},{\"title\":\"How Agentic AI Is Revolutionizing Software Development: From Code Generation to Autonomous Engineering (2026)\",\"url\":\"https://www.brilworks.com/blog/agentic-ai-software-development/\"},{\"title\":\"Claude Code Vs Cursor 2026: Opus 4.6 Just Changed Everything (I Tested Both) - AI Tool Analysis\",\"url\":\"https://aitoolanalysis.com/claude-code-vs-cursor/\"},{\"title\":\"We Tested 15 AI Coding Agents (2026). Only 3 Changed How We Ship.\",\"url\":\"https://www.morphllm.com/ai-coding-agent\"},{\"title\":\"Mighty Blog - 9 Best AI Coding Agents in 2026, Ranked\",\"url\":\"https://www.mightybot.ai/blog/coding-ai-agents-for-accelerating-engineering-workflows\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's an overview of the real capabilities of Claude Code, Cursor, Devin, and other autonomous coding agents in 2026:\n\n## Claude Code\n\nClaude Code has the best reasoning of any AI coding tool — when it plans a change, the plan is almost always right on the first try. Freshly upgraded with Opus 4.6 (released February 5, 2026), it is an agent-first tool that lives in your terminal and does work for you. Claude Code reads entire codebases, understands the relationships between modules, and makes coordinated changes across multiple files in a single operation. Claude Code shipped Agent Teams where multiple AI agents communicate directly with each other, coordinate through shared task lists, and hook into your company's systems via MCP.\n\n## Cursor\n\nCursor is an IDE-first editor that helps you write code faster while you stay in the driver's seat. Cursor now runs cloud agents on isolated VMs that test their own code, record videos of their work, and produce merge-ready pull requests. Over 35% of proposed fixes get merged without modification, and BugBot's resolution rate climbed from 52% to over 70%, and it flags an average of 0.7 bugs per PR.\n\n## Devin\n\nDevin by Cognition is the most autonomous coding agent on the market and runs in a fully sandboxed cloud environment with its own IDE, browser, terminal, and shell. You assign a task and Devin plans, writes, tests, and submits a PR without intervention. Cognition slashed pricing from $500/month to $20/month Core plus $2.25 per ACU (Agent Compute Unit), with one ACU being roughly 15 minutes of active work.\n\n## Performance Benchmarks\n\nFrom 49% SWE-bench Verified (Claude 3.5 Sonnet, Oct 2024) to 88% on Aider (GPT-5, Feb 2026) — performance roughly doubled in 18 months. SWE-bench Verified, which tests agents against real GitHub issues, is the most widely used benchmark, with top scores currently exceeding 80%.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\nIn February 2026, every major tool shipped multi-agent in the same two-week window: Grok Build (8 agents), Windsurf (5 parallel agents), Claude Code Agent Teams, Codex CLI (Agents SDK), Devin (parallel sessions).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"ce8061fc-3963-47ef-af32-508849a4e21c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:14.217Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"61a41e00-6d68-461d-8fe0-5281ebfa6a7a","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
