{"parentUuid":"154bf66e-9eb1-40f9-b574-1c2864f4ee78","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017phKY7afj9izj5E4CH3HrD","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI power dynamics concentration 2026 who controls artificial intelligence\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Power Dynamics: Do We Control AI, or Does It Control Us? — Bloomsbury Intelligence and Security Institute (BISI)\",\"url\":\"https://bisi.org.uk/reports/artificial-intelligence-power-dynamics-who-controls-ai\"},{\"title\":\"Eight ways AI will shape geopolitics in 2026 - Atlantic Council\",\"url\":\"https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/dispatches/eight-ways-ai-will-shape-geopolitics-in-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"How 2026 Could Decide the Future of Artificial Intelligence | Council on Foreign Relations\",\"url\":\"https://www.cfr.org/articles/how-2026-could-decide-future-artificial-intelligence\"},{\"title\":\"AI's Role in Reshaping Power Distribution - Future of Life Institute\",\"url\":\"https://futureoflife.org/project/ai-role-in-reshaping-power-distribution/\"},{\"title\":\"MCAI Innovation Vision: The Power Stack, How Energy Infrastructure Became the New AI Battleground\",\"url\":\"https://www.mindcast-ai.com/p/ai-data-center-energy-series\"},{\"title\":\"AI is moving power from governments to tech companies - Rest of World\",\"url\":\"https://restofworld.org/2026/ai-government-regulation-tech-giants/\"},{\"title\":\"Power, Policy & AI: The Rules of the Race in 2026 | Dell\",\"url\":\"https://www.dell.com/en-us/blog/power-policy-ai-the-rules-of-the-race-in-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Power, connectivity and the next phase of the AI supercycle | World Economic Forum\",\"url\":\"https://www.weforum.org/stories/2026/01/power-connectivity-and-the-next-phase-of-the-ai-supercycle/\"},{\"title\":\"Powering the AI Era – FP Analytics\",\"url\":\"https://fpanalytics.foreignpolicy.com/2025/05/20/artificial-intelligence-electricity-demand/\"},{\"title\":\"AI's Power Crunch: Six Trends That Will Decide Who Wins the Next Decade\",\"url\":\"https://www.powermag.com/ais-power-crunch-six-trends-that-will-decide-who-wins-the-next-decade/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what the current landscape shows about AI power dynamics and concentration in 2026:\n\n## Corporate Concentration\n\nThe concentration of AI development within major technology corporations causes unprecedented centralisation of power, enabling these entities to influence behaviour, shape discourse, and extract economic value from human dependency relationships. Sovereignty is migrating from public institutions to private actors, and those who control AI increasingly shape the conditions under which humanity governs itself.\n\n## Geopolitical Competition\n\nRather than a single controlling force, AI control is becoming a geopolitical contest. Throughout 2025, technological breakthroughs from both the United States and China ratcheted up the competition for AI dominance between the superpowers. Smaller and developing states gain a voice but remain structurally dependent on the major powers that control the bulk of AI talent, capital, and computing power.\n\n## Infrastructure as Power\n\nPower has become AI's central bottleneck, driving tech giants to create their own and reviving every available energy source, with whoever wins that power advantage winning the AI race. Additionally, nations with abundant, accessible energy will gain a strategic edge in the AI race.\n\n## Governance Challenges\n\nThe European Union pushes a rights- and risk-based regulatory model, while the United States favors voluntary standards to preserve innovation and security flexibility, and China promotes inclusive cooperation while defending state control over data and AI deployment.\n\nThe picture suggests AI control is concentrated among major tech corporations and competing nation-states, with infrastructure and energy access becoming increasingly critical to power dynamics.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"cc255c79-be9a-408a-a9d2-3cd507ee26b9","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:23.614Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"154bf66e-9eb1-40f9-b574-1c2864f4ee78","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
