{"parentUuid":"74f04dd8-5ae2-4fb2-bcb7-d992f4d5b397","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01VYnBj2QWKVsMAqfsJaMsvR","toolUseID":"toolu_01VYnBj2QWKVsMAqfsJaMsvR","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:35.112Z","uuid":"ddc2e905-a4da-4564-b44f-9fd49d3ff737","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"392919bf-3ad3-4295-ac2d-af9b53c52ded","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VYnBj2QWKVsMAqfsJaMsvR","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"public perception AI 2026 sentiment fear excitement fatigue survey\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Mapping public perception of artificial intelligence: Expectations, risk–benefit tradeoffs, and value as determinants for societal acceptance - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S004016252500335X\"},{\"title\":\"Public Perception of AI: Sentiment and Opportunity\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2407.15998v1\"},{\"title\":\"Exploring excitement counterbalanced by concerns towards AI technology using a descriptive-prescriptive data processing method | Humanities and Social Sciences Communications\",\"url\":\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41599-024-02926-5\"},{\"title\":\"What the public thinks about AI and the implications for governance | Brookings\",\"url\":\"https://www.brookings.edu/articles/what-the-public-thinks-about-ai-and-the-implications-for-governance/\"},{\"title\":\"Frontiers | AI competence and sentiment: a mixed-methods study of attitudes and open-ended reflections\",\"url\":\"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/artificial-intelligence/articles/10.3389/frai.2025.1658791/full\"},{\"title\":\"Public Opinion | The 2024 AI Index Report | Stanford HAI\",\"url\":\"https://hai.stanford.edu/ai-index/2024-ai-index-report/public-opinion\"},{\"title\":\"With AI’s rise, hope and anxiety - Rochester BeaconRochester Beacon\",\"url\":\"https://rochesterbeacon.com/2025/12/24/with-ais-rise-hope-and-anxiety/\"},{\"title\":\"What Americans Really Think About AI Algorithms: Public Confidence and Transparency in Government - Cornell Brooks Public Policy\",\"url\":\"https://publicpolicy.cornell.edu/masters-blog/what-americans-really-think-about-ai-algorithms-public-confidence-and-transparency-in-government/\"},{\"title\":\"What the data says about Americans’ views of artificial intelligence | Pew Research Center\",\"url\":\"https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/12/key-findings-about-how-americans-view-artificial-intelligence/\"},{\"title\":\"Public Opinion | The 2025 AI Index Report | Stanford HAI\",\"url\":\"https://hai.stanford.edu/ai-index/2025-ai-index-report/public-opinion\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what recent surveys reveal about public perception of AI in 2026:\n\n## Overall Sentiment: Cautious and Growing Concern\n\n52% of Americans are more concerned than excited about AI in daily life, compared with just 10% who say they are more excited than concerned. More Americans are concerned today than they were when this question was first asked in 2021, when 37% said they were more concerned than excited.\n\n## Emotional Responses and Sentiment Shifts\n\nRecent surveys show mixed emotions. A 2023 survey found that U.K. and U.S. respondents most commonly reported feeling \"nervous\" about AI (29% and 23%, respectively), followed by \"hopeful\" (17% in both countries) and \"excited\" (17% and 16%, respectively).\n\nMore recent data indicates an increase in negative emotions: A recent survey of the U.S. public shows that feelings of skepticism (+8%) and overwhelm (+6%) have markedly increased between December 2024 and March 2025, with feelings of excitement having decreased by 5 percentage points.\n\n## Geographic and Demographic Variations\n\nSentiment differs significantly by region. A large majority believe AI-powered products and services offer more benefits than drawbacks in countries like China (83%), Indonesia (80%), and Thailand (77%), while in contrast, only a minority share this view in Canada (40%), the United States (39%), and the Netherlands (36%).\n\n## Key Concerns\n\nMany Americans worry that AI could exacerbate inequality, threaten jobs, infringe on privacy, or make opaque decisions with serious consequences, often without meaningful human oversight.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"089e12be-ffde-4756-a152-f74e3ecc251b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:35.111Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"392919bf-3ad3-4295-ac2d-af9b53c52ded","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"089e12be-ffde-4756-a152-f74e3ecc251b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_016siM36T3rxjuzMghV9XUBM","toolUseID":"toolu_016siM36T3rxjuzMghV9XUBM","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:37.636Z","uuid":"643d3db4-ae3e-4e48-b796-667e6526690c","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"2bd83e01-6e41-4c72-9511-9aaef4241855","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016siM36T3rxjuzMghV9XUBM","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI consciousness debate 2026 sentience research serious\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"What if AI becomes conscious and we never know | ScienceDaily\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2025/12/251221043223.htm\"},{\"title\":\"“Existential risk” – Why scientists are racing to define consciousness | ScienceDaily\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/01/260131084626.htm\"},{\"title\":\"We may never be able to tell if AI becomes conscious, argues philosopher | University of Cambridge\",\"url\":\"https://www.cam.ac.uk/research/news/we-may-never-be-able-to-tell-if-ai-becomes-conscious-argues-philosopher\"},{\"title\":\"The Evidence for AI Consciousness, Today | AI Frontiers\",\"url\":\"https://ai-frontiers.org/articles/the-evidence-for-ai-consciousness-today\"},{\"title\":\"Are We Building Sentient Machines? Anil Seth on Consciousness, AI, and the Illusion of Reality - Wharton Human-AI Research\",\"url\":\"https://ai.wharton.upenn.edu/updates/are-we-building-sentient-machines-anil-seth-on-consciousness-ai-and-the-illusion-of-reality/\"},{\"title\":\"What if AI is already conscious? Sentience explained - LSE\",\"url\":\"https://www.lse.ac.uk/lse-player/what-if-ai-is-already-conscious-sentience-explained\"},{\"title\":\"Is AI really conscious—or are we bringing it to life? | Scientific American\",\"url\":\"https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/is-ai-really-conscious-or-are-we-bringing-it-to-life/\"},{\"title\":\"Philosopher argues AI consciousness may remain unknowable\",\"url\":\"https://www.spacedaily.com/reports/Philosopher_argues_AI_consciousness_may_remain_unknowable_999.html\"},{\"title\":\"We may never be able to tell if AI becomes conscious, argues philosopher\",\"url\":\"https://techxplore.com/news/2025-12-ai-conscious-philosopher.html\"},{\"title\":\"There is no such thing as conscious artificial intelligence | Humanities and Social Sciences Communications\",\"url\":\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41599-025-05868-8\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's an overview of the AI consciousness and sentience research debate in 2026:\n\n## Current State of the Debate\n\nThe AI consciousness debate in 2026 has become increasingly serious and polarized. Scientists warn that rapid advances in AI and neurotechnology are outpacing our understanding of consciousness, creating serious ethical risks.\n\n## Major Positions\n\nThere are two main camps in the debate:\n\n1. **Functionalist believers**: Believers argue that if an AI system can replicate the \"software\" – the functional architecture – of consciousness, it will be conscious even though it's running on silicon chips instead of brain tissue.\n\n2. **Biological skeptics**: Sceptics argue that consciousness depends on the right kind of biological processes in an \"embodied organic subject\". Even if the structure of consciousness could be recreated on silicon, it would merely be a simulation that would run without the AI flickering into awareness.\n\n## Key Scientific Concerns\n\n\"Understanding consciousness is one of the most substantial challenges of 21st-century science -- and it's now urgent due to advances in AI and other technologies. If we become able to create consciousness -- even accidentally -- it would raise immense ethical challenges and even existential risk.\"\n\n## Sentience vs. Consciousness\n\nAn important distinction emerging in the debate is between consciousness and sentience. According to Dr. Tom McClelland, consciousness alone isn't the ethical tipping point anyway; sentience, the capacity to feel good or bad, is what truly matters.\n\n## Emerging Research Evidence\n\nSome researchers are finding evidence worth investigating. Frontier AI systems are exhibiting a constellation of properties that resist easy dismissal. Researchers are starting to more systematically investigate this question, and they're finding evidence worth taking seriously. Over just the last year, independent groups across different labs, using different methods, have documented increasing signatures of consciousness-like dynamics in frontier models.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"121dc141-2f36-45a9-a93f-0ba23eb60a1a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:37.636Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2bd83e01-6e41-4c72-9511-9aaef4241855","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
