{"parentUuid":"e3ae6825-1d9f-4843-aff6-484bf2661ee2","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CDTKiZPn6EFSVjDng9eyfs","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"open source vs closed AI winning 2026 who benefits\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Open Source vs Proprietary AI: Who Wins in the 2026 Race?\",\"url\":\"https://www.analyticsinsight.net/artificial-intelligence/open-source-vs-proprietary-ai-will-open-code-last-in-2026\"},{\"title\":\"The Coming Disruption: How Open-Source AI Will Challenge Closed-Model Giants | California Management Review\",\"url\":\"https://cmr.berkeley.edu/2026/01/the-coming-disruption-how-open-source-ai-will-challenge-closed-model-giants/\"},{\"title\":\"Open Source vs Closed AI: Where the Battle Stands in 2026 | Future Humanism\",\"url\":\"https://futurehumanism.co/articles/open-source-vs-closed-ai-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Open-Source LLMs vs Closed: Unbiased Guide for Innovative Companies [2026]\",\"url\":\"https://hatchworks.com/blog/gen-ai/open-source-vs-closed-llms-guide/\"},{\"title\":\"AI open models have benefits. So why aren’t they more widely used? | MIT Sloan\",\"url\":\"https://mitsloan.mit.edu/ideas-made-to-matter/ai-open-models-have-benefits-so-why-arent-they-more-widely-used\"},{\"title\":\"Open Source AI vs Closed AI: Pros and Cons (2026 Guide)\",\"url\":\"https://aiagentskit.com/blog/open-source-vs-closed-ai/\"},{\"title\":\"Understanding Open Source vs. Closed Source in AI\",\"url\":\"https://blog.udemy.com/open-source-vs-closed-source-ai/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Trends 2026 – LLM Statistics & Industry Insights\",\"url\":\"https://llm-stats.com/ai-trends\"},{\"title\":\"The foundation model divide: Mapping the future of open vs. closed AI development - CB Insights Research\",\"url\":\"https://www.cbinsights.com/research/report/future-of-foundation-models-open-source-closed-source/\"},{\"title\":\"Is Closed AI Holding Us Back? Why Open Source Might Win the Race | ARC Advisory Group\",\"url\":\"https://www.arcweb.com/blog/closed-ai-holding-us-back-why-open-source-might-win-race\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what the 2026 AI landscape shows about open source vs. closed models and who benefits:\n\n## Current Status: It's Not a Clear Winner\n\nThe days of closed models being obviously superior are over. Instead, open source models now match or exceed proprietary alternatives for many use cases. However, OpenAI's o1 model class represents capabilities open source hasn't matched, with complex multi-step reasoning still proprietary territory.\n\n## Key Performance Metrics\n\nOpen models achieve about 90% of the performance of closed models at the time of release but quickly make up the difference. Open source models are improving three times faster year-over-year, and the performance gap has narrowed to the point where it genuinely depends on your specific needs.\n\n## Who Benefits?\n\nThe real winners are organizations taking a **hybrid approach**:\n\n- A hybrid approach is winning with enterprises: they look to closed-source frontier models for the most sophisticated applications and open-source smaller models for edge and specialized use cases.\n\n- Startups are increasingly adopting this technology because it allows them to eliminate their expensive API dependencies.\n\n- Governments are investing in creating their own national AI systems, which helps emerging countries break away from foreign dependencies on technology.\n\n## Cost Advantage for Open Source\n\nClosed models cost users, on average, six times as much as open ones, and optimal reallocation of demand from closed to open models could save the global AI economy about $25 billion annually.\n\n## The Bottom Line\n\nThe smartest organizations start with closed source AI models to get to market fast and prove their concept, then strategically migrate high-value components to open source as their team matures and customization becomes critical.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"013d6beb-95d5-47ce-9a16-f3317aa97a84","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:49.910Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e3ae6825-1d9f-4843-aff6-484bf2661ee2","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
