{"parentUuid":"68be9e07-6628-433c-8271-5543638bc1ae","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01EoHELiAyATySUhZMFBKr2C","toolUseID":"toolu_01EoHELiAyATySUhZMFBKr2C","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:01.825Z","uuid":"713c3ae9-1cee-4c98-9c63-14ac25f5c3e7","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"691e714c-6840-450d-b5d9-a0871e856542","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EoHELiAyATySUhZMFBKr2C","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI alignment values-aligned AI beyond safety 2026 meaning purpose\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"AI Alignment: A Contemporary Survey | ACM Computing Surveys\",\"url\":\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3770749\"},{\"title\":\"AI Safety, Alignment, and Interpretability in 2026 | Zylos Research\",\"url\":\"https://zylos.ai/research/2026-02-09-ai-safety-alignment-interpretability\"},{\"title\":\"My AGI safety research—2025 review, '26 plans\",\"url\":\"https://www.alignmentforum.org/posts/CF4Z9mQSfvi99A3BR/my-agi-safety-research-2025-review-26-plans\"},{\"title\":\"MATS Research\",\"url\":\"https://www.matsprogram.org/\"},{\"title\":\"Hype and harm: Why we must ask harder questions about AI and its alignment with human values | Brookings\",\"url\":\"https://www.brookings.edu/articles/hype-and-harm-why-we-must-ask-harder-questions-about-ai-and-its-alignment-with-human-values/\"},{\"title\":\"RESEARCH PAPER JANUARY 2026 Legal Alignment for Safe and Ethical AI\",\"url\":\"https://aigi.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Kolt-Caputo-et-al.-2026-Legal-Alignment-for-Safe-and-Ethical-AI.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"AI alignment - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AI_alignment\"},{\"title\":\"How we think about safety and alignment | OpenAI\",\"url\":\"https://openai.com/safety/how-we-think-about-safety-alignment/\"},{\"title\":\"The Challenges of AI Alignment: Recent Advances and Insights - This Week in Science\",\"url\":\"https://thisweekinsciencenews.com/blog/2026/01/01/the-challenges-of-ai-alignment-recent-advances-and-insights/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Alignment 2026: Explained Simply\",\"url\":\"https://www.aitechboss.com/ai-alignment-2026/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about AI alignment, values-aligned AI, and their relationship to safety in 2026:\n\n## AI Alignment: Definition and Scope\n\nAI alignment refers to ensuring that an AI system's objectives match some target, which is variously defined as the goals of the system's designers or users, widely shared values, objective ethical standards, legal requirements, or the intentions its designers would have if they were more informed and enlightened.\n\n## Values-Aligned AI Beyond Safety\n\nValue alignment focuses on embedding ethical and social norms into AI decision-making. The field has evolved to encompass more than just safety:\n\nAssurance in AI systems is categorized into three parts: Safety Evaluations, Interpretability, and Human Value Verification—verifying whether AI systems can align with human values, ethics, and social norms and satisfying the high-level need of AI systems' integration to human society.\n\n## Meaning and Purpose in 2026\n\nIn 2026, the values of alignment may be very different depending on the use case, particularly with AI promising remarkable breakthroughs across sectors, from assistive technology in education to supporting patients in health care.\n\nAI alignment encompasses both the normative problem of specifying which values are desirable or appropriate for AI systems and the technical problem of ensuring AI systems give effect to those values when making decisions and taking actions.\n\nThe field recognizes that alignment goes beyond preventing harm—it's about ensuring AI systems actively reflect human values and purposes in context-sensitive ways across diverse applications and communities.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"8532dbf1-1bdf-41f8-bd33-72f99946bbe0","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:01.825Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"691e714c-6840-450d-b5d9-a0871e856542","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
