{"parentUuid":"f67b6983-ec1f-4882-9d98-85ea0c23db3b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a5b760f7bd0b5bba3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016yG8M51DsXxDm9yokWiKjj","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"dharmic AI ethical AI telos-aligned consciousness-aware AI systems 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"The Future Of Hinduism In The AI Age: Spirituality Vs. Artificial Intelligence - AdikkaChannels\",\"url\":\"https://adikkachannels.com/the-future-of-hinduism-in-the-ai-age-spirituality-vs-artificial-intelligence/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Alignment: The Dharmic Imperative – Indian Knowledge Systems and AI\",\"url\":\"https://iksai.hcommons.org/2026/01/24/ai-alignment-the-dharmic-imperative/\"},{\"title\":\"Beyond Western Frameworks: Why AI Ethics Needs a Dharmic Perspective | by Priya Krishnamoorthy | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@priya.krishnamoorthy/beyond-western-frameworks-why-ai-ethics-needs-a-dharmic-perspective-53796e284632\"},{\"title\":\"The Ethics of AI: What Would the Mahabharata Say About Machine Consciousness? — Dharma, Duty, and Moral Agency in Artificial Beings - Ashim Dutta\",\"url\":\"https://ashimdutta.in/2025/09/09/the-ethics-of-ai-what-would-the-mahabharata-say-about-machine-consciousness-dharma-duty-and-moral-agency-in-artificial-beings/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Meets Sanatan Dharma. AI follows Sanatan Dharma | by Manik Roy | AIdion | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/aidion/ai-meets-sanatan-dharma-ef7a61eb4281\"},{\"title\":\"Frontiers | The anthropomorphization of AI and the concept of Buddhist compassion in human-machine interaction\",\"url\":\"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2025.1583565/full\"},{\"title\":\"For Dharmic Robots\",\"url\":\"https://openthemagazine.com/essay/for-dharmic-robots\"},{\"title\":\"Buddhistdoor View: The Dharmic Conundrum of AI - Buddhistdoor Global\",\"url\":\"https://www.buddhistdoor.net/features/buddhistdoor-view-the-dharmic-conundrum-of-ai/\"},{\"title\":\"Scientists Race to Define AI Consciousness Before Technology Outpaces Ethics | ACM Project - Artificial Consciousness Research\",\"url\":\"https://theconsciousness.ai/posts/scientists-race-define-ai-consciousness-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"The Ethics Of AI Consciousness In 2026\",\"url\":\"https://ndebeyond.com/the-ethics-of-ai-consciousness-in-2026/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found on dharmic AI, ethical AI, telos-aligned, and consciousness-aware AI systems in 2026:\n\n## Dharmic AI Frameworks\n\nDharmic AI emphasizes ethics boards infused with dharmic wisdom rather than utilitarian cost-benefit analysis, drawing on ancient insights from the Manusmriti, Bhagavad Gita, and Yoga Sutras to align technology with spiritual evolution. Dharmic AI regulatory frameworks adopt principles from Sanatana Dharma—protecting all life, nurturing balance, and ensuring justice contextualized to individuals.\n\n## Telos-Aligned AI Perspectives\n\nA dharmic framework asks: What is the true purpose of this system? What values drive its creation? Are those motives aligned with human flourishing? Dharmic traditions offer concepts of consciousness, intention, and interconnectedness that enable designing more humane AI systems, enriching Western ethical frameworks.\n\n## Consciousness-Aware AI Systems in 2026\n\nJanuary and February 2026 mark an inflection point in artificial consciousness research, with multiple independent research teams publishing urgent calls for better frameworks to define and detect machine consciousness. A January 2026 framework argues that consciousness comprises multiple semi-independent dimensions, with systems potentially conscious in some dimensions while lacking consciousness in others.\n\nSome experts in 2026 argue that very advanced AI models display behaviors that might signal at least a basic kind of machine consciousness.\n\n## Buddhist-Inspired AI Ethics\n\nThe four immeasurables—Metta, Karuna, Mudita, and Upekkha—in Buddhism offer a more adaptable ethical framework compared to other religious doctrines for guiding robotic development.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"c59dd319-c27d-4666-b40b-8d6887f1fa56","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:03.104Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f67b6983-ec1f-4882-9d98-85ea0c23db3b","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
